How to use AWS CLI : It makes API calls to services over HTTPS. You can monitor your calls using CloudTrail. Outbound connections on TCP port 443 must be enabled in order to perform calls.

a) Sign up for an aws account
b) Go to AWS Console -> My account

Access keys consist of an access key ID and secret access key :: Generate IAM access keys in place of root

a) Open IAM console: https://console.aws.amazon.com/iam/ -> Users -> Select or create new and assign poweruser policy
Note:
b) Access Id: ********************
c) Secret Access key: ********************

Install awscli using pip on aws machine :: 

sudo pip install awscli --ignore-installed six

Check system/instance status ::

aws ec2 describe-instance-status
